        <h1 class="credit-broking-exact-page__title">Credit Broking Permission for Motor Dealers</h1>
        <p class="ccr009-hero__lead">Credit broking permission is one of the most common FCA permissions held by motor dealers.</p>
        <p class="ccr009-hero__lead">If your dealership introduces customers to vehicle finance providers, assists with finance applications or helps customers access finance products, credit broking permission may be required.</p>
        <p class="ccr009-hero__lead">Many motor dealers are surprised to learn that they can be carrying out regulated activities even though they are not lending money themselves. This is because introducing a customer to a finance provider can constitute credit broking and fall within the FCA's regulatory framework.</p>
        <p class="ccr009-hero__lead">Understanding how credit broking applies to motor dealers is important because it often forms a key part of FCA authorisation, ongoing compliance obligations and consumer credit reporting requirements.</p>
        <div class="ccr009-actions">
          <a class="ccr009-btn ccr009-btn--primary" href="/contact#send-message">Start an FCA Authorisation Enquiry</a>
